      • isBranchingCrossRoad

        public static boolean isBranchingCrossRoad(Ilot block,
                                           double sizeThreshold,
                                           double surfDistThreshold,
                                           IFeatureCollection<NoeudRoutier> simples,
                                           IFeatureCollection<RondPoint> roundabouts)

        Determine if a road block object is a branching crossroad or not. Uses graph measures (3 nodes with degree 3) and shape measures. A branching crossroad should be triangle shaped. This version of the method does not use the Gothic spatial queries but requires the cartagen objects as entries.

        Parameters:
        block - : the tested road block
        sizeThreshold - : the maximum area of a branching crossroad (2500 mÂ² advised)
        surfDistThreshold - : the maximum surfacic distance between the block and the triangle formed by the three nodes of the block. (0.5 advised)
        simples - : the simple crossroads of the network
        roundabouts - : the roundabouts of the network
        Returns:
        true if the block is a branching crossroad.

      • characteriseBranching

        public boolean characteriseBranching()
        find the characteristic roads of the branching crossroad. The link with the roundabouts has to be instanciated before to optimise the characterisation
        Returns:
        true if the characterisation was OK, false if there was a problem.
